Sentencas: Active sites for oxygen reduction reaction in strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM)/scandia-stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) composite cathode of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is visualized in microstructure scale by oxygen isotope labeling.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: In order to quench a reaction, a SOFC power generation equipment with a nozzle for direct helium gas impinging jet to the cell is prepared.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: A typical electrolyte-supported cell is operated by supplying O-18(2) at 1073 K and, abruptly quenched to room temperature.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: During the quench, the temperature of the cell is decreased from 1073 K to 673 K in 1 s.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: The O-18 concentration distribution in the cross section of the quenched cathode is obtained by secondary ion mass spectrometry (SIMS) with a spatial resolution of 50 nm.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode

Sentencas: The obtained O-18 mapping gives the first visualization of highly distributed active sites in the composite cathode both in macroscopic and particle scales.
Titulo: Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode
Microstructure-scaled active sites imaging of a solid oxide fuel cell composite cathode
